
COPY ~%MOD_FOLDER%/Druid/TotemicDruid/2DAs~ ~OVERRIDE~
COPY ~%MOD_FOLDER%/Druid/TotemicDruid/SPELLS~ ~OVERRIDE~

ACTION_IF FILE_EXISTS_IN_GAME ~CLABDR02.2DA~ BEGIN
COPY_EXISTING ~CLABDR02.2DA~ ~OVERRIDE~
  REPLACE_TEXTUALLY ~GA_SPCL621~ ~****      ~
  LPF set_clab_2da_entries INT_VAR f_MinLevel = 1 f_MaxLevel = 1 STR_VAR f_Entry = GA_C0D2_A0 END
  PRETTY_PRINT_2DA
END

OUTER_SPRINT kit_description ~TOTEMIC DRUID: This Druid closely identifies with a particular animal, an animal that <PRO_HESHE> feels represents <PRO_HISHER> spirit. This grants <PRO_HIMHER> a special connection to the animal kingdom, and <PRO_HESHE> is able to call upon their spirits to aid <PRO_HIMHER>.

Advantages:
– May use the Totemic Guardian special ability.

TOTEMIC GUARDIAN: The totemic druid is persistently guarded by an animal spirit. The spirit manifests when the totemic druid enters battle and remains until the battle ends. The spirit animal can be controlled, increases in power as the summoner gains in druid levels. The totemic druid may select a spirit animal to be guarded by once per day, with each providing different bonuses to all druids, shamans, rangers and barbarians within a 15-ft. radius of them.
  BEAR'S ENDURANCE: The summoner gains a +10% bonus to physical resistances and a +1 bonus to Saving Throws vs. Death.
  WOLF'S TENACITY: The summoner gains a +10% bonus to all damage dealt, with an additional +1 bonus to melee damage.
  LION'S COURAGE: The summoner gains a +1 bonus to THAC0, Morale and Saving Throw vs. Spells.
  SNAKE'S SWIFTNESS: The summoner gains a +1 bonus to Armor Class, Movement Rate and Saving Throws vs. Breath.

– 5th level: May use the Spirit's Protection ability while a spirit animal is present. This ability is cast from the spirit animal's special abilities rather than the summoner's own.

SPIRIT'S PROTECTION: The totemic druid may command their spirit animal to bestow their power upon a targeted creature for one turn. The spirit animal disappears for the duration and grants their bonuses to the target regardless of their class. Once the effect expires, the spirit animal manifests at the summoner's side once more.

– 8th level: Totemic Guardian bonuses increase to +15%/+2 for their respective effects.
– 10th level: Spirit's Protection heals the target for 50% of their maximum hit points.
– 12th level: Spirit's Protection removes negative mind-affecting effects from the target and grants them protection from similar effects for the duration.
– 14th level: Totemic Guardian bonuses increase to +20%/+3 for their respective effects.
– 14th level: Spirit's Protection may now be cast on dead allies, restoring them to life and then providing their usual bonuses. However, the spirit animal will be unable to manifest itself again until eight hours have passed. Additionally, so long as the totemic druid is being guarded by a spirit, they are protected from instant death effects as per a Death Ward spell. If they would take lethal damage while under this protection, the spirit animal expends its energies to protect them from the attack while applying Spirit's Protection on them.
– 15th level: Totemic Guardian bonuses increase to +25%/+4 for their respective effects. Spirit's Protection heals the target for 100% of their maximum hit points.

Disadvantages:
– Cannot use shapeshift.
– If the totemic druid's spirit animal is defeated in battle or uses its energies to protect its summoner from death, it will be unable to manifest unless a full turn passes and the battle is still ongoing. If this occurs, the totemic druid suffers a -2 penalty to casting speed and a 25% chance to miscast spells for one turn.~

LAF ~GET_KIT_STRREF~ STR_VAR kit_name = ~TOTEMIC_DRUID~ RET kit_strref END
STRING_SET_EVALUATE kit_strref ~%kit_description%~

// ICONS

DEFINE_ACTION_FUNCTION cd_new_portrait_icon
  INT_VAR string = 0
  STR_VAR bam_file = "****"
  RET     icon
  BEGIN

  COPY_EXISTING ~statdesc.2da~ ~override~
    COUNT_2DA_ROWS 3 count
    READ_2DA_ENTRY (count - 1) 0 3 icon
    SET icon += 1

  APPEND ~statdesc.2da~ ~%icon% %string% %bam_file%~ UNLESS ~%bam_file%~

END

LAF cd_new_portrait_icon INT_VAR string = RESOLVE_STR_REF(~Spirit: Bear~) STR_VAR bam_file = C0D2_I1 RET C0D2_I1 = icon END
LAF cd_new_portrait_icon INT_VAR string = RESOLVE_STR_REF(~Spirit: Wolf~) STR_VAR bam_file = C0D2_I2 RET C0D2_I2 = icon END
LAF cd_new_portrait_icon INT_VAR string = RESOLVE_STR_REF(~Spirit: Lion~) STR_VAR bam_file = C0D2_I3 RET C0D2_I3 = icon END
LAF cd_new_portrait_icon INT_VAR string = RESOLVE_STR_REF(~Spirit: Snake~) STR_VAR bam_file = C0D2_I4 RET C0D2_I4 = icon END

