COPY_EXISTING ~C0D2_1Z.SPL~ ~OVERRIDE~
SAY NAME1 ~Command: Spirit's Protection~
SAY UNIDENTIFIED_DESC ~This ability allows the Totemic Druid to directly bestow their spirit animal's blessings upon the targeted ally. It may only be used out of combat, when the spirit animal has not manifested.

The totemic druid may command their spirit animal to bestow their power upon a targeted creature for one turn. The spirit animal disappears for the duration and grants their bonuses to the target regardless of their class. Once the effect expires, the spirit animal manifests at the summoner's side once more.

10th level: Spirit's Protection heals the ally for 50% of their maximum hit points.

12th level: Spirit's Protection may now be cast on dead allies, restoring them to life and then providing their usual bonuses. However, the spirit animal will be unable to manifest itself again until eight hours have passed. Additionally, so long as the totemic druid is being guarded by a spirit, they are protected from instant death effects as per a Death Ward spell. If they would take lethal damage while under this protection, the spirit animal expends its energies to protect them from the attack and heal them for 30% of their maximum hit points.

14th level: Spirit's Protection may now be cast on dead allies, restoring them to life and then providing their usual bonuses. However, the spirit animal will be unable to manifest itself again until eight hours have passed. Additionally, so long as the totemic druid is being guarded by a spirit, they are protected from instant death effects as per a Death Ward spell. If they would take lethal damage while under this protection, the spirit animal expends its energies to protect them from the attack and heal them for 30% of their maximum hit points.~

